article_id:1223,category_name:Events,title_name:A Facility Event Revival, The Hunt for Harmony, Is Now Live!,image_path:https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/cedea8d72b40b1d62dc4484e19676cc9.png,message:<div>A facility event revival, The Hunt for Harmony, went live <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1586757600"></span>!</div><div><img src="https://dragalialost.akamaized.net/attached/information/images/cedea8d72b40b1d62dc4484e19676cc9.png"></div><div>It&#39;s time for the sylvans&#39; Vernal Banquet, where rabbit-eared people from far and wide gather to celebrate. The main event is an egg hunt, and whoever collects the most eggs is granted one wish.</div><div>As the prince, Sarisse, and Luca vie for the prize, Luca spots some familiar faces... It&#39;s his childhood friends, also competing in the egg hunt!</div><div>Who will collect the most eggs and win the competition AND a wish?</div><div><br></div><div>■Event Overview</div><div>In The Hunt for Harmony, you can acquire an event-exclusive facility: the Drago&ntilde;ata. If you play the event, you&#39;ll have the chance to build one for your Castle Grounds!</div><div><br></div><div>The Drago&ntilde;ata increases the stats of water-attuned adventurers. It also boosts the damage that adventurers deal against enemies in event quests. Progress through the event story and level up your Drago&ntilde;ata.</div><div><br></div><div>Adventurers can equip event-specific wyrmprints to receive more papier-m&acirc;ch&eacute;, which is used to upgrade the Drago&ntilde;ata, from these quests. Wyrmprints are good for more than just that, though, so try to get ahold of them to get the most out of this event!</div><div><br></div><div>Please note that special effects conferred by event-specific wyrmprints do not apply if you begin a quest during the event period but complete the quest after the event period has ended.</div><div><br></div><div>■Additions</div><div>・New maximum level unlocked for the event facility!</div><div>The Drago&ntilde;ata event facility can now be leveled up to a maximum of level 35.</div><div><br></div><div>・New difficulty level added!</div><div>A new difficulty level, Nightmare, has been added to the challenge battle.</div><div>The Nightmare difficulty challenge battle will be available starting at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1586930400"></span>.</div><div>Additionally, players must complete the Master difficulty challenge battle to attempt Nightmare difficulty.</div><div>Note: Even if you complete the Master difficulty challenge battle, you will not be able to play the Nightmare difficulty battle until it is available.</div><div><br></div><div>Nightmare difficulty requires the same amount of stamina as the Expert and Master difficulties, and you will receive the same amount of eggsploration points.</div><div>Once per day, when you clear Nightmare difficulty, you can get a Grand Bounty.</div><div>Note: The Grand Bounty you receive is randomly selected from a set of rewards.</div><div><br></div><div>■Event Duration<br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1586757600"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1587362399"></span><br><br>■Reward Availability Period<br><span class="local_date" data-local_date="1586757600"></span> to <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1587967199"></span><br><br>■Event-Exclusive Facility: Drago&ntilde;ata<br>This facility increases the stats of water-attuned adventurers.<br>It also confers a special effect that lets you deal more damage to enemies in these event quests.<br>The strength of this effect increases as you level up the Drago&ntilde;ata.<br>This effect only applies for the duration of this event.<br>To level up the Drago&ntilde;ata, you&#39;ll need papier-m&acirc;ch&eacute;, which you can find in these event quests.<br><br>■Upgrade Item: Papier-M&acirc;ch&eacute;<br>You can get these from the story quests, boss battle, and extra boss battle for The Hunt for Harmony facility event revival.<br><br>■Boss Battles<br>Boss battles are quests where you can face off against boss enemies that appear in the event story. Rewards vary depending on the difficulty cleared. This quest can be played either solo or co-op.<br><br>■Extra Boss Battles<br>Although the difficulty level of extra boss battles is higher than the event boss battle on Expert difficulty, the rewards are generous and the battles do not cost stamina or getherwings.<br>Extra boss battles occasionally appear after clearing the event boss battle on Expert difficulty. They will disappear again after being successfully cleared. Once the conditions for the quest are met, you can unlock it repeatedly. This quest can be played either solo or co-op.<br><br>・Even if you clear the boss battle several times in a row using the auto-repeat feature, the extra boss battle will only become available once at most.<br><br>■Challenge Battles<br>Challenge battles are high-difficulty quests limited to solo play, and are available in Expert, Master, and Nightmare difficulties. The Expert difficulty challenge battle is unlocked after completing the event boss battle on Expert difficulty, and the Master difficulty challenge battle will unlock when you complete the Expert difficulty challenge battle. The Nightmare difficulty challenge battle will become available at <span class="local_date" data-local_date="1586930400"></span>, and you must complete the Master difficulty challenge battle to play it.<br>・Even if you complete the Master difficulty challenge battle, you will not be able to play the Nightmare battle until it is available.<br><br>These quests will have you testing your strength against waves of enemies. If you fail to reach the last wave in Expert or Master difficulty, you will still receive rewards for the ones you did clear, but in Nightmare difficulty you must complete the final wave to earn rewards.<br>Finally, the drop rate for rewards differs based on the difficulty.<br>・The drop rate for rewards in Nightmare difficulty is the same as Master difficulty.<br><br>Once per day when you clear Nightmare difficulty, you can get a Grand Bounty.<br>・The Grand Bounty you receive is randomly selected from a set of rewards.<br><br>■Eggsploration Point Rewards<br>Eggsploration points are event-exclusive points that can be earned by clearing event quests. Collect them to earn all kinds of rewards!<br><br>■Treasure Trade Rewards<br>You can earn mushroom medleys and woodland herbs by playing event quests and trade them for various rewards on the Treasure Trade menu.<br>What&#39;s more, in this event you&#39;ll be able to trade papier-m&acirc;ch&eacute;, which is required to level up the Drago&ntilde;ata event facility, for mushroom medleys and woodland herbs, which are only used in the Treasure Trade, and vice versa.<br><br>・Papier-m&acirc;ch&eacute; obtained when The Hunt for Harmony event was held in the past will carry over to this event revival, but unless you participate in the event revival, you will not be able to trade it for other items in the Treasure Trade.</div><div><br></div><div>■Event Bonus<br>The following wyrmprints will have bonus effects during The Hunt for Harmony event revival.<br>・A Mother&#39;s Love<br>・Forest Bonds<br>・Egg-Shaped Dreams<br>・Tiny Drago&ntilde;atas<br>If you equip these wyrmprints and clear event quests, you&#39;ll get even more papier-m&acirc;ch&eacute; and eggsploration points.<br><br>You can get A Mother&#39;s Love from the event&#39;s Treasure Trade or as an eggsploration points reward. Forest Bonds, Egg-Shaped Dreams, and Tiny Drago&ntilde;atas are available in the Treasure Trade for wyrmprints.<br>・The amount of event bonus effect differs based on the wyrmprint and how much the wyrmprint has been unbound.<br><br>■Endeavors<br>These endeavors can only be attempted for the duration of the event. They are separated into Daily and Limited variations. By accomplishing these endeavors, you can receive various rewards.<br><br>■Castle Stories<br>New stories have been added to Castle Stories. You can read it by using Looking Glasses, which can be obtained as eggsploration point rewards.<br>&nbsp;<br>Notes:<br>1. You can see more details about this event by tapping Help on the event page.<br>2. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign to participate.<br>3. Players must have completed up to Chapter 2 / 2-1 (Normal) of the main campaign in order to play co-op.<br>4. If the event ends while you are playing an event quest, the quest will continue until results have been determined and you will be able to gain the rewards shown.<br><br>Thank you for playing Dragalia Lost.</div>,start_time:1586757600,update_time1586324035